The paper discusses the use of virtual reality (VR) in neurosurgery, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and user interface design (SI). The paper also mentions the use of open-source tools, which falls under the category of cybernetics (CY). Additionally, the paper involves the visualization of anatomical structures, which could fall under computer vision (CV) or graphics (GR).
